quran[4]{c,v,t}:
  18,50,"When We said to the angels, ‘Prostrate before Adam,’ they prostrated, but not Iblis. He was one of the jinn, so he transgressed against his Lord’s command. Will you then take him and his offspring for guardians in My stead, though they are your enemies? How evil a substitute for the wrongdoers"
  18,51,"I did not make them witness to the creation of the heavens and the earth, nor to their own creation, nor do I take those who mislead others as assistants"
  18,52,"The day He will say [to the polytheists], ‘Call those whom you maintained to be My partners,’ they will call them, but they will not respond to them, for We shall set an abyss between them"
  18,53,"The guilty will sight the Fire and know that they are about to fall in it, for they will find no way to escape it"